edu.mit.jwi.data
Interface IDictionaryDataSource

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractCachingDataSource, WordnetFile
public interface IDictionaryDataSource

Objects that implement this interface mediate between the IDictionary and the data the is contained in the dictionary data resources. They typically are assigned a name (e.g., verb.data, for the data resource pertaining to verbs) and a content type. A string key is used to find a particular piece of data in the resource. The IDictionaryFile object then returns a text string that can be parsed to produce a data object (e.g., an ISynset or IIndexWord object). To speed up searches in the data, it is recommended the data contained in the resource backing the IDictionaryFile be ordered, and a comparator that takes advantage of this order be provided to the internal search mechanism of the class.

iterator

java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String> iterator(java.lang.String key)
Returns an iterator that will iterator over lines in the data resource, starting at the line specified by the given key. If said line is not found, or the key is null, the iterator will start at the beginning of the file.
